    "The result is wrong, but when we ask for an explanation, we receive a misleading explanation for the wrong prediction.",
    "This example indicates that a more challenging, not LLM-generated dataset may in fact trigger more explanations for wrong labels.",
    "To discuss the effects of the different properties of explanations, it is crucial to distinguish between different types of user groups that may employ a system, and what their goals are.",
    "Adadi and Berrada (2018) identify four reasons to seek explanations: to justify decisions, to (enhance) control, to improve models, and to discover new knowledge.",
    "Mittelstadt et al. (2019) name actual interpretability (faithfulness), trustworthiness, accountability, accessibility, comprehensibility, and usefulness as common goals."
